The paper deals with the performance evaluation and optimization of cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper leverages stochastic geometry for system-level analysis. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
